<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 7:05AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Snow and poor visibility along the Hi-line this morning...
Areas of snow and poor visibility will affect locations along the
Highway 2 corridor from just west of Havre to Marias Pass.
Visibility will fall below one mile at times, with snow
accumulations of an inch or two on grassy areas, while some
slippery areas are possible on roadways.
Additionally, wind gusts near 50 mph will also cause some areas of
blowing snow.</description>
